## Running Promises in Parallel

`await` runs sequentially. If operations don't depend on each other, you can run them in parallel using `Promise.all`.

```javascript
async function parallelRead() {
  const [data1, data2] = await Promise.all([
    fs.readFile('file1.txt', 'utf8'),
    fs.readFile('file2.txt', 'utf8')
  ]);
  console.log(data1, data2);
}
```

`Promise.all` waits for all promises to resolve (or rejects if any fails).
